SIMPLE: misuse
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Misuse
<hw>Mis*use"</hw> <pr>(m⟦icr⟧s*⟦umac⟧z")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>m⟦eacute⟧suser</ets>. See <er>Mis-</er>, prefix from French, and
<er>Use</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To treat or use improperly; to use
to a bad purpose; to misapply; <as>as, to <ex>misuse</ex> one's
talents</as>.</def> <rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sweet poison of <qex>misused</qex> wine.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To abuse; to treat ill.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O, she <qex>misused</qex> me past the endurance of a block.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To maltreat; abuse; misemploy;
misapply.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misuse</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Misuse
<hw>Mis*use"</hw> <pr>(m⟦icr⟧s*⟦umac⟧s")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Wrong use; misapplication; erroneous or improper use.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Words little suspected for any such <qex>misuse</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Violence, or its effects.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misusement</ent>⟦br⟧
